hip and its owners </li>\n  <li>an up-to-date crew list with names, dates of birth and addresses</li>\n  <li>a list of anyone on board who is under 18 or exempt from a crew agreement</li>\n  <li>&lsquo;contractual clauses&rsquo; for each crew member</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>A crew agreement can be for a maximum of 12 months. After this period, a new agreement must be drawn up.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>What goes in a contractual clause</h2>\n\n<p>These must include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the name of the crew member</li>\n  <li>a description of the journey(s) that the agreement relates to</li>\n  <li>the crew member&rsquo;s job description</li>\n  <li>details of their pay, hours and leave </li>\n  <li>details of notice and how the crew agreement is to be terminated</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The Maritime and Coastguard Agency (<abbr title=\"Maritime and Coastguard Agency\">MCA</abbr>) provides guidance on drawing up crew agreements for merchant ships and yachts.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/mca/mgn148.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Approval of Crew Agreements – Merchant ships (MGN148)' (PDF, 134KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Approval of crew agreements – merchant ships (MGN148)’ (PDF, 134KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/mca/mgn149docs.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Approval of Crew Agreements – Yachts (MGN149)' (PDF, 134KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Approval of crew agreements – yachts (MGN149)’ (PDF, 134KB) </a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Contact the <abbr title=\"Maritime and Coastguard Agency\">MCA</abbr> for advice on drawing up a crew agreement.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Maritime and Coastguard Agency (<abbr title=\"Maritime and Coastguard Agency\">MCA</abbr>)</strong><br />\n0845 603 2431</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>What to do once you&rsquo;ve drawn up a crew agreement</h2>\n\n<ol class=\"steps\">\n<li><p>Get every crew member to sign it when they jo